# Implementation Plan - Theme Alignment & UI Polish

Align all recent UI refactorings (Attendance grid, Action Dropdowns) with the project's dark/light mode theme system by using standard CSS variables and utility patterns.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> I will be replacing hardcoded Tailwind colors (e.g., `indigo-600`, `emerald-500`) with theme-aware variables (e.g., `var(--brand-primary)`, `var(--success)`) across [Attendance.jsx](file:///c:/Users/mathi/Desktop/AntiGravity%20Demos/HRMS%20Singapore/client/src/pages/Attendance.jsx), [Leave.jsx](file:///c:/Users/mathi/Desktop/AntiGravity%20Demos/HRMS%20Singapore/client/src/pages/Leave.jsx), [Payslip.jsx](file:///c:/Users/mathi/Desktop/AntiGravity%20Demos/HRMS%20Singapore/client/src/pages/Payslip.jsx), and [EmployeeKETs.jsx](file:///c:/Users/mathi/Desktop/AntiGravity%20Demos/HRMS%20Singapore/client/src/pages/EmployeeKETs.jsx).

## Proposed Changes

### [Attendance.jsx](file:///c:/Users/mathi/Desktop/AntiGravity Demos/HRMS Singapore/client/src/pages/Attendance.jsx)
- **Container Hierarchy**: Update the matrix zone to use `bg-[var(--bg-card)]` and the filter bar to use `bg-[var(--bg-input)]` (the standard "input on card" pattern).
- **Color Variables**: Replace `indigo-600/500/400` with `var(--brand-primary)` or `var(--brand-primary-light)`.
- **Consistency**: Use `dark:bg-white/5` or similar subtle overlays where appropriate to match the rest of the app.

### Action Dropdowns ([Leave.jsx](file:///c:/Users/mathi/Desktop/AntiGravity Demos/HRMS Singapore/client/src/pages/Leave.jsx), [Payslip.jsx](file:///c:/Users/mathi/Desktop/AntiGravity Demos/HRMS Singapore/client/src/pages/Payslip.jsx), [EmployeeKETs.jsx](file:///c:/Users/mathi/Desktop/AntiGravity Demos/HRMS Singapore/client/src/pages/EmployeeKETs.jsx))
- **Style Alignment**: Change the "Actions" selectable dropdown background from the purple tint (`bg-brand-primary/10`) to the standard `bg-[var(--bg-input)]` with a brand-aware border (`border-[var(--brand-primary)]/30`).
- **Focus States**: Ensure focus/hover states use theme-consistent shadows and colors.

